Colin:

> Check out Peter Gutmann's Message Digest Cipher.  His SFS partition
> encryptor for MS-DOS implements this.
> 
> The idea is that you use the Transform() function of MD5 or SHS as a
> block cipher, with a 128 or 160-bit block and a 512-bit key.
> 
> It only goes one way, but if you use it in CFB mode, you only need it to
> go one way.  And it's very fast on 32-bit machines. -- 
>  -Colin

Thanks for the pointer. Yes, I've examined MDC and discarded it. I'm uneasy
about the vulnerability to chosen-plaintext attacks. I'm currently looking
at variant approaches which conceal the input to the hash functions from an
attacker.

